WEBVTT

00:01.827 --> 00:03.525
ADULT ADAM: Back in the '80s,
I loved Halloween,

00:03.699 --> 00:05.353
especially the costumes,

00:05.527 --> 00:08.965
and no one made dressing up
more special than my Pops.

00:09.139 --> 00:11.533
But this was gonna be my
first Halloween without him,

00:11.707 --> 00:13.535
and things were bound to be
a little different.

00:13.709 --> 00:14.840
[DOORBELL RINGS]

00:15.015 --> 00:16.320
♪♪♪♪

00:16.494 --> 00:17.234
The hell is this? It's Halloween.

00:17.408 --> 00:18.453
Traditionally,
people knock on doors.

00:18.627 --> 00:19.671
They're still doing that?

00:19.845 --> 00:21.543
Uch.

00:21.717 --> 00:23.110
MURRAY:
Candy's in the bowl!

00:23.284 --> 00:24.763
[DOOR CLOSES]Don't touch any Reese's Cups.
They're mine.

00:24.937 --> 00:27.114
Adam! Dave Kim
and his brother are here!

00:27.288 --> 00:28.811
I'm clearly not
Dave Kim.

00:28.985 --> 00:30.247
And I'm definitely not
his brother.

00:30.421 --> 00:31.248
Yeah, I don't care.
What's with the hat?

00:31.422 --> 00:32.597
I'm the shy and mousy
love interest,

00:32.771 --> 00:34.338
Adrian from Rocky.

00:34.512 --> 00:36.558
And I'm Rocky's corner man,
the gruff but loveable Mickey.

00:36.732 --> 00:38.908
It'll be more obvious
with Adam as our Rocky Balboa.

00:39.082 --> 00:40.779
An Italian
throwing punches.

00:40.953 --> 00:41.563
[CHUCKLES]
There's something new.

00:41.737 --> 00:42.738
What's this?

00:42.912 --> 00:44.261
I don't remember
the Italian Stallion

00:44.435 --> 00:45.654
wearing ThunderCatsPJs.

00:45.828 --> 00:48.831
Sorry, guys, but I have
a tiny tickle in my throat.

00:49.005 --> 00:51.007
[COUGHS WEAKLY]
Do you hear that?

00:51.181 --> 00:53.966
Not really.It's there,
and it hurts a ton.

00:54.141 --> 00:55.142
I thought it was just
a tiny tickle.

00:55.316 --> 00:57.100
An incredibly painful
tiny tickle.

00:57.274 --> 00:58.406
This whole thing
is incredibly painful.

00:58.580 --> 00:59.276
I'll take some
peanut butter cups.

00:59.450 --> 01:00.712
MURRAY: Only one!

01:00.886 --> 01:02.149
If all we have left
are Abba-Zabas,

01:02.323 --> 01:03.411
everyone's in trouble.

01:03.585 --> 01:05.326
So you're not coming to
the Halloween dance?

01:05.500 --> 01:07.719
I should probably just
stay home and heal up,

01:07.893 --> 01:08.938
but eat some candy corn
for me.

01:09.112 --> 01:10.113
Candy corn is ass.

01:10.287 --> 01:11.984
It has a chalky
and waxy texture,

01:12.159 --> 01:13.334
and don't get me started
on its mouthfeel.

01:13.508 --> 01:14.813
How dare you?

01:14.987 --> 01:16.859
It's chewy
and just a bit crumbly,

01:17.033 --> 01:19.557
and it holds its shape just
enough for a good tooth sink.

01:19.731 --> 01:21.603
Brea, thoughts?Not really.

01:21.777 --> 01:22.952
As soon as
you said "mouthfeel,"
I kind of shut down.

01:23.126 --> 01:24.649
At least we drove over here
to hear the news in person.

01:28.740 --> 01:31.178
Perfect 98.6. Gah!

01:31.352 --> 01:33.571
When did you take that?
Where did you take that?

01:33.745 --> 01:35.399
Why are you lying
about throat tickles?

01:35.573 --> 01:37.662
Fine. The truth is

01:37.836 --> 01:40.926
Halloween was a special night
for me and Pops.

01:41.101 --> 01:43.146
I'm just gonna
sit this one out.
No big whoop.

01:43.320 --> 01:45.148
Of course, Schmoopie.
No whoop at all.

01:45.322 --> 01:46.845
♪♪♪♪

01:47.019 --> 01:49.196
This is
a huge [BLEEP] whoop.

01:49.370 --> 01:51.111
I've got to restore
Adam's Halloween spirit.

01:51.285 --> 01:52.329
Well, we all have our stuff.

01:52.503 --> 01:54.375
For example, me,

01:54.549 --> 01:57.117
I'm gonna go watch a special
Halloween "Night Court."

01:57.291 --> 01:58.901
And you, you've got to heat up
this four-meat lasagna

01:59.075 --> 02:00.294
and bring it to me.

02:00.468 --> 02:02.905
And so my mom did
everything she could

02:03.079 --> 02:04.907
to get me back in the groove
of my favorite holiday.

02:05.081 --> 02:07.039
She tried treats. Your favorite!

02:07.214 --> 02:09.651
Ooey-gooey chocolate chewy
for my Schmooey.

02:09.825 --> 02:11.348
Nope.

02:11.522 --> 02:12.349
She tried tricks.

02:12.523 --> 02:13.916
♪♪♪♪

02:14.090 --> 02:15.657
[LAUGHS] Mwah.

02:15.831 --> 02:17.093
Not a chance.

02:17.267 --> 02:18.921
She even tried...
whatever this was.

02:19.748 --> 02:21.184
Aah!

02:21.358 --> 02:22.794
Get it?
It's like in Psycho.

02:22.968 --> 02:24.187
It is psycho!

02:24.361 --> 02:25.536
The only thing psycho

02:25.710 --> 02:27.408
is how broad
your shoulders have gotten.

02:27.582 --> 02:28.887
You're my little
Iron Man!

02:29.061 --> 02:30.237
Oh, God!

02:30.411 --> 02:32.021
Just use
the knife already!

02:32.195 --> 02:34.023
♪♪ I'm twisted up inside

02:34.197 --> 02:36.721
♪♪ But nonetheless,
I feel the need to say

02:39.898 --> 02:41.204
♪♪ I don't know the future

02:41.378 --> 02:45.121
♪♪ But the past keeps getting
clearer every day

02:45.295 --> 02:47.732
It was October 27th,
1980-something,

02:47.906 --> 02:50.822
and my brother Barry was not
exactly in the Halloween mood.

02:50.996 --> 02:52.694
[ MONSTER MASH
PLAYING THROUGH WALLS]

02:52.868 --> 02:55.000
Enough Monster Mash!

02:55.175 --> 02:56.915
We get it! [SIGHS]

02:57.089 --> 02:57.742
Monsters need
to let loose, too!

02:58.961 --> 03:00.310
What's the matter, babe?

03:00.484 --> 03:01.790
You usually
love Halloween.

03:01.964 --> 03:04.009
It's the one day a year your
candy habit seems reasonable.

03:04.184 --> 03:06.055
If I want to get into
the medical school
of my choice,

03:06.229 --> 03:07.187
I have to bear down.

03:07.361 --> 03:08.840
That's so inspiring.

03:09.014 --> 03:10.538
When I'm a lawyer,

03:10.712 --> 03:12.279
I'm gonna handle
all your malpractice suits.

03:12.453 --> 03:13.932
It won't matter
who you kill or disfigure,

03:14.106 --> 03:15.412
I will always be
right by your side.

03:15.586 --> 03:17.501
Aww.Yeah, aww.

03:17.675 --> 03:20.112
Come get your treat,
you nasty trickster.

03:20.287 --> 03:22.027
Blech. Can you guys
do that somewhere else?

03:22.202 --> 03:23.507
Like, nowhere and never?

03:23.681 --> 03:25.117
And why
would I hide it?

03:25.292 --> 03:26.945
I'd happily demonstrate
my affection for Joanne

03:27.119 --> 03:28.991
on the 50-yard line
of the Fiesta Bowl.

03:29.165 --> 03:30.340
Mm, that's so hot.

03:30.514 --> 03:31.689
The refs would totally
throw a flag

03:31.863 --> 03:33.038
for illegal use
of our hands and faces.

03:33.213 --> 03:34.866
Sure. Love finds a way.

03:35.040 --> 03:36.433
Hey, Barry, could I get
my popcorn machine back?

03:36.607 --> 03:37.695
How dare you?

03:37.869 --> 03:39.741
I need it when I want
to make and eat popcorn.

03:39.915 --> 03:41.308
No, I understand why
you borrowed it,

03:41.482 --> 03:43.223
but Erica and I are gonna have
a Halloween movie marathon.

03:43.397 --> 03:45.094
Blood, guts,
and gore? Fun.

03:45.268 --> 03:46.617
Nah, Geoff's not really
into that,

03:46.791 --> 03:48.010
so instead,
we're watching the movies

03:48.184 --> 03:50.099
of America's goofball
sweetheart, Goldie Hawn.

03:50.273 --> 03:52.319
In Overboard,she's
a rich lady who gets amnesia

03:52.493 --> 03:53.494
and ends up shacking up
with Kurt Russell

03:53.668 --> 03:55.147
and his lousy kids.

03:55.322 --> 03:56.061
On the silver screen,
it's a romp,

03:56.236 --> 03:57.585
but in the real world,

03:57.759 --> 03:58.542
it's kidnapping
and sexual slavery.

03:58.716 --> 04:00.805
I want this back
first thing tomorrow.

04:00.979 --> 04:02.633
Again, it's mine. So, what are
you guys doing tonight?

04:02.807 --> 04:03.895
Barry's studying,

04:04.069 --> 04:05.245
and I don't really
celebrate Halloween.

04:05.419 --> 04:06.898
I was briefly a Wiccan,

04:07.072 --> 04:08.248
and once you dabble
in the occult,

04:08.422 --> 04:10.293
tonight feels
very amateur.

04:10.467 --> 04:11.773
Well, we got
the popcorn thingy,
so we should rush out.

04:11.947 --> 04:13.296
Bye, Joanne. Big Tasty.

04:13.470 --> 04:15.342
Big Tasty?
Who's that?

04:15.516 --> 04:16.995
You know.
It's Barry's nickname.

04:17.169 --> 04:18.562
I do not know.
Since when?

04:18.736 --> 04:19.911
Since forever.

04:20.085 --> 04:21.130
I've been
crushing the rap game

04:21.304 --> 04:22.566
with my mad rhymes
and sick flow.

04:22.740 --> 04:25.003
You rap? Wow.

04:25.177 --> 04:26.396
How do you not know this
about me?

04:26.570 --> 04:28.006
Maybe you just haven't
done it in awhile.

04:28.180 --> 04:29.356
You've been so focused
on medical school.

04:29.530 --> 04:31.183
It's a good thing.Good thing?

04:31.358 --> 04:32.576
My own girlfriend
doesn't know

04:32.750 --> 04:34.361
how dope I am
at spitting lyrics.

04:34.535 --> 04:35.536
Show me,
show me, show me.

04:35.710 --> 04:37.755
Give me a topic.
Literally anything.

04:37.929 --> 04:39.583
That pencil.A-one--

04:39.757 --> 04:41.759
[RAPPING] ♪♪ This pencil,
It's filled with lead

04:41.933 --> 04:43.979
♪♪ It's also got wood
Did I mention the lead?

04:44.153 --> 04:44.806
♪♪ W-What? What? ♪♪

04:44.980 --> 04:45.937
What?

04:46.111 --> 04:47.417
I lost my magic.

04:47.591 --> 04:49.637
We all lose things --
like the time.

04:49.811 --> 04:50.551
[CHUCKLES]
Would you look at that?

04:50.725 --> 04:51.769
It's --Huh.

04:51.943 --> 04:53.380
Don't worry.
I liked it, Large Yummy.

04:53.554 --> 04:55.077
It's Big Tasty.

04:55.251 --> 04:57.906
While Barry feared he'd lost
his hip-hop superpower,

04:58.080 --> 05:01.039
my mom was hellbent on winning
back my love for Halloween.

05:01.213 --> 05:03.085
Hey! I was kind of
watching that!

05:03.259 --> 05:04.608
Ben, I need your help.No thanks.

05:04.782 --> 05:05.392
You don't even know
what it is yet.

05:05.566 --> 05:07.263
I get the sense
it involves me, so...

05:07.437 --> 05:08.917
Bevy, don't bother the man.

05:09.091 --> 05:10.832
He's never participated
in life in any way.

05:11.006 --> 05:12.181
Why would he start now?

05:12.355 --> 05:14.183
Eh, let her finish so I can
pretend to consider it.

05:14.357 --> 05:16.098
Adam needs some Halloween
grandpa time.

05:16.272 --> 05:18.187
Hmm. No.

05:18.361 --> 05:19.493
You don't have a choice.
You're doing it.

05:19.667 --> 05:22.539
Oh, this one with
the hair and the ideas.

05:22.713 --> 05:23.584
All right,
tell me where to stand.

05:23.758 --> 05:25.673
Yay, his heart
is full and ready!

05:25.847 --> 05:28.415
With that,
my Halloween was back on.

05:28.589 --> 05:30.112
Sort of. Let's just
get this over with.

05:30.286 --> 05:31.940
I don't like
looking like a Canadian.

05:32.114 --> 05:34.464
Also, your cardigan isn't
exactly screaming "scary."

05:34.638 --> 05:35.944
You want to know
what's really scary?

05:36.118 --> 05:38.076
I had three UTIs this year,
so hustle up.

05:38.250 --> 05:39.730
I'm gonna have to
take a tinkle soon.

05:39.904 --> 05:42.646
And so began the worst
Halloween movie ever.

05:42.820 --> 05:43.908
How am I gonna
murder in this?

05:44.953 --> 05:46.346
My face is so hot.

05:46.520 --> 05:47.956
Won't they know
the goalie did it?

05:48.130 --> 05:51.220
So he's killing the campers.
Can't say that I blame him.

05:51.394 --> 05:52.874
Sleeping on the ground
like a bunch of schnooks.

05:53.048 --> 05:54.789
And cut!
I think we got it.

05:54.963 --> 05:56.225
Got it?

05:56.399 --> 05:57.618
I haven't stabbed
any horny kids yet.

05:57.792 --> 05:59.402
But you have
killed my spirit.

05:59.576 --> 06:00.838
That's a wrap
on Pop-Pop.Really?

06:01.012 --> 06:02.840
I'm here.

06:03.014 --> 06:04.102
I'm wearing this thing
that smells like your brother.

06:04.276 --> 06:06.235
No offense, Pop-Pop,
it's just--

06:06.409 --> 06:07.889
It's not the same as doing it
with your other grandpa.

06:08.063 --> 06:09.064
I get it.

06:09.238 --> 06:09.934
I'm sorry.

06:10.108 --> 06:11.936
Ah, don't be.

06:12.110 --> 06:13.285
Everybody loved
that guy.

06:13.460 --> 06:14.896
A little too smiley
for my taste, but you do you.

06:15.070 --> 06:16.506
Thank you
for understanding.

06:16.680 --> 06:18.029
Well, thanks for understanding
you're gonna drive me home.

06:18.203 --> 06:20.031
While I was saddled with
giving Pop-Pop a lift,

06:20.205 --> 06:21.990
my brother was busy
rounding up help

06:22.164 --> 06:23.644
to bring back Big Tasty.

06:23.818 --> 06:24.906
What's the emergency,
Barry?

06:25.080 --> 06:26.429
I was in the middle of
Private Benjamin.

06:26.603 --> 06:27.212
A sheltered,
wealthy lady in the army?

06:27.387 --> 06:28.736
Sir, no, sir!

06:28.910 --> 06:31.086
The emergency is
Big Tasty is back!Ha!

06:31.260 --> 06:32.696
And he's got
a million-dollar idea.

06:32.870 --> 06:35.307
After hearing Monster Mash
over and over,

06:35.482 --> 06:36.744
it hit me.

06:36.918 --> 06:39.573
There's no surer way
to pop super-stardom

06:39.747 --> 06:43.141
than writing and performing
a novelty Halloween hit.

06:43.315 --> 06:45.230
What?Damn right, what?

06:45.405 --> 06:46.536
And all he needs is your help
to come up with

06:46.710 --> 06:47.885
the theme, music,
and lyrics.

06:48.059 --> 06:49.147
Isn't that everything?No.

06:49.321 --> 06:51.498
I had the idea
for the idea.

06:51.672 --> 06:54.283
Legally, anything that's said
from here on out, I own.

06:54.457 --> 06:55.893
What?I got one.

06:56.067 --> 06:57.547
♪♪ We did the bob

06:57.721 --> 06:59.288
♪♪ We did the apple bob ♪♪

06:59.462 --> 07:01.159
That's just Monster Mash
with different words.

07:01.333 --> 07:02.944
Nuh-uh.
It's about apples.

07:03.118 --> 07:05.033
Why is this something
you needed immediately?

07:05.207 --> 07:06.643
Aren't you kind of focused
on becoming a doctor?

07:06.817 --> 07:09.037
Why do I have to
just be one thing?

07:09.211 --> 07:11.387
Can't I be
Dr. Big Tasty, MD?

07:11.561 --> 07:13.476
Sure, you can. But I
don't think you're gonna
get a lot of patients.

07:13.650 --> 07:14.695
I'll get
all the patients!

07:14.869 --> 07:17.741
Even your
stupid eye patients.

07:17.915 --> 07:20.483
I'll cure their blindness
with my bedside manner

07:20.657 --> 07:22.833
and crazy syncopation.What?

07:23.007 --> 07:25.923
Let me clear it up for you.
I need an international smash!

07:26.097 --> 07:28.796
Topic, cobwebs. Go!

07:28.970 --> 07:31.233
I love you, Barry, but I think
you're wasting your time.

07:31.407 --> 07:32.974
And mine.Fine!

07:33.148 --> 07:34.802
But every year
during this time,

07:34.976 --> 07:36.543
you'll have to explain
to your kids,

07:36.717 --> 07:38.545
"I know the guy
who wrote that song,

07:38.719 --> 07:40.068
"but I wouldn't
support him

07:40.242 --> 07:42.549
"by coming up with the idea
and writing it for him!"

07:42.723 --> 07:44.855
While Geoff shot down
Barry's novelty-song dreams,

07:45.029 --> 07:47.336
I was heading into
an All-Hallows nightmare.

07:47.510 --> 07:48.598
Thanks for helping me

07:48.772 --> 07:50.252
lug your mother's
pumpkin bread up here.

07:50.426 --> 07:51.949
They are surprisingly
hard and sharp

07:52.123 --> 07:53.864
for something
supposedly made with love.

07:54.038 --> 07:55.344
I can stick those in the wall
of the john. [CHUCKLES]

07:55.518 --> 07:57.215
No leak's gonna get by
those walnuts.

07:57.389 --> 07:58.869
Welp,
I look forward to the tale

07:59.043 --> 08:00.741
of how these loaves saved
your bathroom at Thanksgiving.

08:00.915 --> 08:01.872
Until then.

08:02.046 --> 08:03.395
Whoa, whoa. Wait.
Where you going?

08:03.570 --> 08:04.658
I thought you were
gonna stick around

08:04.832 --> 08:06.573
and help me shoo away
those costumed moochers.

08:06.747 --> 08:07.965
As much fun
as that sounds,

08:08.139 --> 08:10.446
I think I'm just gonna
head home, go to bed,

08:10.620 --> 08:11.578
and wake up
when Halloween's over.

08:13.667 --> 08:16.147
Oh, son of a bitch!
Someone stole my pumpkin.

08:16.321 --> 08:17.758
Pumpkin?

08:17.932 --> 08:19.107
You don't decorate
for Halloween.

08:19.281 --> 08:20.325
Halloween?

08:20.500 --> 08:21.326
No, I was waiting
for it to ripen

08:21.501 --> 08:22.850
in this nice October air.

08:23.024 --> 08:24.025
That was my special
soup pumpkin.

08:24.199 --> 08:25.766
Soup pumpkin?You're damn right.

08:25.940 --> 08:27.594
It was a rare
albino gourd.

08:27.768 --> 08:29.030
That was
weeks of soup.

08:29.204 --> 08:30.510
What am I supposed to
do about it?

08:30.684 --> 08:31.685
You're gonna help me
find the bastard who took it.

08:31.859 --> 08:34.557
Or we go to the supermarket,
and I'll buy you

08:34.731 --> 08:36.516
all the weird-colored
vegetables your heart desires.

08:36.690 --> 08:37.865
And let those bastards win?
No way.

08:38.039 --> 08:38.648
We're gonna go right now.

08:39.519 --> 08:40.302
We're Halloweening.

08:43.784 --> 08:45.002
It was Halloween,

08:45.176 --> 08:47.091
but instead of the quiet
night at home I wanted,

08:47.265 --> 08:49.790
I was having a garbage time
with Pop-Pop.

08:49.964 --> 08:52.053
I understand we're looking for
a white pumpkin

08:52.227 --> 08:54.055
that will yield you
months of soup,

08:54.229 --> 08:56.057
but why exactly are we
wearing trash bags?

08:56.231 --> 08:57.798
We gotta blend in
with costumes.

08:57.972 --> 08:59.669
This isn't a costume.
It's a Hefty Cinch Sak.

08:59.843 --> 09:01.497
Ooh, Cinch Sak.

09:01.671 --> 09:03.847
Someone's mommy pays for
the good stuff.

09:04.021 --> 09:05.501
Now just ring the doorbell,
ask for candy.

09:05.675 --> 09:06.589
I'll case the house.

09:06.763 --> 09:07.764
That's your plan?

09:07.938 --> 09:10.201
A door-to-door pumpkin search
in trash bags?

09:10.375 --> 09:11.768
Look at you
following along, huh?

09:11.942 --> 09:13.204
Now, you got
that sock I gave you?

09:13.378 --> 09:15.032
I threw it away.Threw it away?

09:15.206 --> 09:16.860
That's grocery store
socks. Now where are you
gonna put the candy?

09:17.034 --> 09:18.122
Your foot
was just in there!

09:18.296 --> 09:20.081
Oh, check you,
Prince of Persia,

09:20.255 --> 09:22.039
too good to eat sweets
from my calf-highs.

09:22.213 --> 09:23.563
Fine! Just give me
the other one, I guess.

09:23.737 --> 09:24.694
[GROANS]

09:24.868 --> 09:26.000
There.

09:26.174 --> 09:27.784
Oh, God.

09:27.958 --> 09:28.872
Why is it damp?

09:29.046 --> 09:29.743
There's a cool mist
in the air.

09:29.917 --> 09:31.658
No, there isn't!

09:31.832 --> 09:33.573
And why is it warm
to the touch?

09:33.747 --> 09:34.835
It's like the towel
they give you at Benihana

09:35.009 --> 09:36.010
before the meal.

09:36.184 --> 09:37.533
Here we are.
Ding-dong we go.

09:38.665 --> 09:39.796
[DOORBELL RINGS]

09:41.276 --> 09:42.451
Trick or treat,
I guess?

09:42.625 --> 09:44.192
What are you
supposed to be?

09:44.366 --> 09:46.107
The only thing that
makes sense is trash.

09:46.281 --> 09:48.326
Well, happy Halloween.

09:48.500 --> 09:50.415
Yeah, happy for you.
Have you seen this?

09:50.590 --> 09:51.678
A poorly drawn circle?

09:51.852 --> 09:53.114
That's a pumpkin.

09:53.288 --> 09:54.376
I don't like your sass,
Zorro.

09:54.550 --> 09:56.421
I'm clearly a witch.Yeah, I bet you are.

09:56.596 --> 09:57.422
Thank you.

09:59.686 --> 10:02.689
When did you draw
a "missing" sign for
a pumpkin?

10:02.863 --> 10:04.908
Just put the Circus Peanuts
in the hot sock
and keep moving.

10:05.082 --> 10:07.694
And so our painful search
for the pumpkin continued.

10:07.868 --> 10:10.131
Come on, already.
Let's knock.

10:10.305 --> 10:12.176
Clearly,
no one's home.

10:12.350 --> 10:14.004
They left a bowl out with
a sign that says, "Take one!"

10:14.178 --> 10:15.702
Oh, I guess they didn't
take my pumpkin.

10:15.876 --> 10:17.181
Nobody can be
that stupid.

10:17.355 --> 10:19.096
Look, I'm just gonna roll up
this, uh, Cinch Sak,

10:19.270 --> 10:20.663
and you can dump it all
in there.

10:20.837 --> 10:22.578
And break
the trick-or-treater's code?
No way.

10:22.752 --> 10:23.884
[CHOIR SINGING]Holy butt paper!

10:25.189 --> 10:26.974
Is this Halloween
or Christmas?

10:27.148 --> 10:28.976
Why are you so excited about
a tree full of toilet paper?

10:29.150 --> 10:30.717
That's enough Charmin
to last me two weeks.

10:30.891 --> 10:32.762
That's a remarkably short
amount of time.

10:32.936 --> 10:34.198
Will you stop squawking
and start gathering?

10:34.372 --> 10:35.939
Now, shimmy up that branch
and get to the top stuff.

10:36.113 --> 10:37.462
Come on.

10:37.637 --> 10:39.029
As my night took another
crappy turn,

10:39.203 --> 10:41.641
Barry was ready to say
good night to Big Tasty.

10:41.815 --> 10:44.513
[SIGHS]
Farewell, dookie rope.

10:44.687 --> 10:46.384
You will never gleam
on my jacked neck again.

10:46.558 --> 10:48.822
What are you doing with
your mom's jewelry?Please.

10:48.996 --> 10:50.562
She would never wear anything
this small and tasteful.

10:50.737 --> 10:51.999
[NECKLACE JANGLES]

10:52.173 --> 10:53.653
I'm burying everything
that was Big Tasty.

10:53.827 --> 10:55.176
Rest in piece,
Kangol hat.

10:55.350 --> 10:57.569
You protected my head
full of sick rhymes.

10:57.744 --> 10:59.702
Stop. You can't
throw away who you are.

10:59.876 --> 11:01.399
And yet, I am.

11:01.573 --> 11:03.401
Adios, Adidas tracksuit.

11:03.575 --> 11:05.229
I'll never rap
or occasionally exercise

11:05.403 --> 11:06.100
in you again.

11:07.971 --> 11:09.756
W-What are you doing?
That's my sad box!

11:09.930 --> 11:12.280
I'm saving Big Tasty.

11:12.454 --> 11:14.717
Now, look."Elvira:
Mistress of the Dark."

11:14.891 --> 11:15.936
Even in
black and white,

11:16.110 --> 11:17.372
she pops off the page,
if you know what I mean.

11:17.546 --> 11:18.982
Oh, I do.

11:19.156 --> 11:21.202
And she's appearing tonight
at a mall in New Jersey.

11:21.376 --> 11:23.552
This is a sign.It is!

11:23.726 --> 11:25.510
It's like the Halloween
spirits have come to save me.

11:25.685 --> 11:26.990
To save Big Tasty.

11:27.164 --> 11:28.426
Now, you're gonna write

11:28.600 --> 11:30.124
the best Halloween rap
of all time.

11:30.298 --> 11:31.603
She'll hear two bars

11:31.778 --> 11:33.301
and sign you
to her spooky record label.

11:33.475 --> 11:35.216
This is
the perfect plan!I know!

11:35.390 --> 11:36.391
And we can
take the train there,

11:36.565 --> 11:37.479
'cause I'm
a little bit drunk.

11:37.653 --> 11:38.741
You just
gave me an idea

11:38.915 --> 11:40.700
for the biggest hit single
in Halloween history--

11:40.874 --> 11:42.571
Monster Train.

11:42.745 --> 11:44.486
Next stop, gold record!
[LAUGHS]

11:44.660 --> 11:47.228
All we need now
are lyrics, music,

11:47.402 --> 11:48.403
and someone
to arrange it all.

11:48.577 --> 11:49.273
Follow me!

11:49.447 --> 11:50.710
Monster Train?

11:50.884 --> 11:52.494
I am 1,000% in.

11:52.668 --> 11:53.930
You're surprisingly
enthusiastic.

11:54.104 --> 11:55.366
May I ask why?

11:55.540 --> 11:57.194
I'm just excited
to hear Elvira's reaction

11:57.368 --> 11:58.543
when you
present her with

11:58.718 --> 12:00.023
your fun and quickly
cobbled together song.

12:00.197 --> 12:01.242
She's in it
for the right reason!

12:01.416 --> 12:02.765
And with that...Thank you.

12:02.939 --> 12:04.985
...Barry set out
to make novelty-music history.

12:05.159 --> 12:06.943
There was howling...A-woo.

12:07.117 --> 12:08.640
Bigger.
More wolf-like.

12:08.815 --> 12:10.381
...rewrites...

12:10.555 --> 12:11.731
Wait, why is the witch taking
the train to Transylvania?

12:11.905 --> 12:13.210
Wouldn't she just
ride her broom?

12:13.384 --> 12:15.082
Good note.
We need to establish

12:15.256 --> 12:17.301
the witch
lost her broom license.

12:17.475 --> 12:19.042
...and lots of
train sound effects.Chug-a-chug-a-chug-a.

12:19.216 --> 12:21.784
Whoo! All aboard,
ghouls and ghoulettes.

12:21.958 --> 12:24.004
Everyone stop
and cherish this moment,

12:24.178 --> 12:25.309
'cause tomorrow,

12:25.483 --> 12:27.790
your simple,
pathetic lives are over.

12:27.964 --> 12:29.879
And when it was over,
they had a song.

12:30.053 --> 12:31.402
Sort of.

12:31.576 --> 12:32.969
Remember,
you have to call me

12:33.143 --> 12:34.623
after Elvira hears this.

12:34.797 --> 12:37.147
I need to know what she says
word for word.

12:37.321 --> 12:40.368
You're a good sister.Sure. Word for word.

12:40.542 --> 12:42.587
While Barry had a ticket
for the "Monster Train,"

12:42.762 --> 12:44.894
my Halloween with Pop-Pop
was off the rails.

12:45.068 --> 12:47.244
Oh-ho-ho!
A tree full of two-ply.

12:47.418 --> 12:48.985
Life doesn't get better.

12:49.159 --> 12:50.639
I sincerely
hope it does.

12:50.813 --> 12:52.510
Oh, right, I forgot.

12:52.684 --> 12:55.731
Boy Iacocca here wipes
his tush with cotton candy.

12:55.905 --> 12:58.081
Cotton candy?
That seems like a big mess.

12:58.255 --> 13:00.127
I just thought, instead of
your nonstop whining,

13:00.301 --> 13:01.998
you might be having
a good time or something.Good time?

13:02.172 --> 13:04.740
No offense, but your hunt
for the Great Albino Pumpkin

13:04.914 --> 13:06.176
couldn't get any worse.

13:06.350 --> 13:07.221
[THUNDER RUMBLES]

13:07.395 --> 13:09.571
Oh, damn it!

13:09.745 --> 13:11.573
Quick,
scurry under that car!

13:11.747 --> 13:14.141
Or how about we can just
jump into this pay phone,

13:14.315 --> 13:15.359
where I can
call my mom?Aah!

13:17.100 --> 13:17.971
Oh.

13:19.233 --> 13:20.147
[COIN DROPS]

13:20.321 --> 13:21.322
[TELEPHONE RINGS]

13:21.496 --> 13:23.324
Adam!
Oh, thank God.

13:23.498 --> 13:24.804
How did you know
it was me?

13:24.978 --> 13:26.718
It takes
only 13 minutes

13:26.893 --> 13:28.155
to get to Pop-Pop's house
and back.

13:28.329 --> 13:29.765
I have been calling
and calling.

13:29.939 --> 13:31.288
Where were you?Here and there.

13:31.462 --> 13:32.637
It's Devil's Night,
Adam.

13:32.812 --> 13:34.465
Every year, six million kids

13:34.639 --> 13:35.902
are abducted
and slaughtered.

13:36.076 --> 13:37.555
That seems high.

13:37.729 --> 13:39.862
You tell that
to my manicurist's
manicurist's son.

13:40.036 --> 13:41.385
She doesn't do
her own nails?

13:41.559 --> 13:42.691
She doesn't do
anything anymore

13:42.865 --> 13:44.432
since her son went
trick-or-treating

13:44.606 --> 13:46.913
and sickos
scavenged his head for parts.

13:47.087 --> 13:49.567
They stole his eyes,
nose, and teeth.

13:49.741 --> 13:52.048
Now every year,
his costume is the same,

13:52.222 --> 13:54.442
human jack-o'-lantern.

13:54.616 --> 13:55.835
But the rest
of the year,

13:56.009 --> 13:57.053
he works in the way, way back
at Circuit City.

13:57.227 --> 13:58.489
So he's doing it!

13:58.663 --> 13:59.969
Murray,
our baby is safe.

14:00.143 --> 14:02.363
Call the police and tell them
to cancel the APB.

14:02.537 --> 14:04.060
I never really called
in the first place.

14:04.234 --> 14:04.756
So what
are you guys doing?

14:04.931 --> 14:06.410
You know,

14:06.584 --> 14:07.890
harassing homeowners
about a white pumpkin

14:08.064 --> 14:09.370
and scaling
a toilet-paper tree.

14:09.544 --> 14:11.111
A toilet-paper tree?

14:11.285 --> 14:13.417
Yeah, it's been basically
the worst Halloween ever.

14:14.462 --> 14:15.419
See ya in a bit.

14:19.293 --> 14:20.598
So, the worst ever, huh?

14:20.772 --> 14:21.425
Oh, yeah.

14:22.818 --> 14:23.819
you know
what I mean.

14:23.993 --> 14:24.994
Oh, yeah. Sure, I do.

14:26.735 --> 14:28.911
Well, it looks like
the rain stopped,

14:29.085 --> 14:30.739
so let's
get you home.

14:30.913 --> 14:32.262
Even worse than
a terrible Halloween

14:32.436 --> 14:34.177
was that I'd hurt Pop-Pop.

14:34.351 --> 14:35.396
There was nothing I could do
to fix it--

14:35.570 --> 14:36.876
Wait!
There it is!

14:37.050 --> 14:38.878
Or was there?

14:39.052 --> 14:40.880
[ANGELIC MUSIC PLAYING]

14:41.054 --> 14:42.055
Adam, wait!

14:43.317 --> 14:44.622
I don't think
that's mine.

14:44.796 --> 14:46.711
Of course it is!
I'm grabbing it.

14:46.886 --> 14:48.496
No, no.
Uh, Adam! Adam! A-Adam!

14:48.670 --> 14:49.889
What the hell?

14:50.063 --> 14:51.542
You stealing my pumpkin,
old man?!

14:51.716 --> 14:53.370
No, no, no, no, no.That's for my
grandpa's soup!

14:53.544 --> 14:54.458
Ow! Whoa!

14:55.546 --> 14:56.504
Ohh. Ahh.

14:56.678 --> 14:58.680
Adam! You okay?

14:58.854 --> 15:00.987
[GROANS]
Not even a little.

15:01.161 --> 15:03.990
As I was down for the count,
Barry was counting on Elvira

15:04.164 --> 15:06.688
to makeMonster Train
a smash hit.

15:06.862 --> 15:07.819
Hello, darlings.

15:07.994 --> 15:09.430
Oh, my God.

15:09.604 --> 15:11.780
You're just as spooky
and beautiful as I imagined.

15:11.954 --> 15:13.477
Um, what can I sign
for you?A record deal.

15:14.957 --> 15:16.219
We, of course,
split the gate,

15:16.393 --> 15:18.656
and I own my likeness,
Big Tasty, in perpetuity.

15:18.830 --> 15:19.962
You'll find it
quite fair,

15:20.136 --> 15:21.703
considering everything
we're bringing to the table.

15:21.877 --> 15:23.923
This is starting to be
a whole thing,

15:24.097 --> 15:27.622
and, uh, there's a line going
back to the Waldenbooks, so...

15:27.796 --> 15:29.711
Where's your Mistress
of the Dark boombox, huh?

15:29.885 --> 15:32.409
I don't have
or even know what that is,

15:32.583 --> 15:34.150
so if you have a song
you want me to hear,

15:34.324 --> 15:35.673
you're just gonna
have to perform it.

15:35.847 --> 15:37.023
In front of all these
freaks and wack jobs?

15:37.197 --> 15:38.241
You mean my fans?

15:38.415 --> 15:39.808
What he means is,

15:39.982 --> 15:42.202
once this crowd of
weirdos and hideous loners

15:42.376 --> 15:44.334
starts grooving
to Big Tasty's hot track,

15:44.508 --> 15:45.683
you won't be able
to say no.

15:45.857 --> 15:47.816
I think
you'd be surprised by

15:47.990 --> 15:49.513
all the things I've said no to
in my life.

15:49.687 --> 15:51.167
Okay.

15:51.341 --> 15:52.864
Jo-Jo!
Drop a funky beat.

15:53.039 --> 15:55.084
[BEAT BOXING]

15:55.258 --> 15:56.999
♪♪ First stop, second stop,
third stop, fourth ♪♪

15:57.173 --> 15:59.523
In that moment,
Big Tasty was back.

15:59.697 --> 16:01.917
He'd dusted off his rhyme
skills for the hottest song

16:02.091 --> 16:04.485
about a commuter train
for monsters ever.

16:04.659 --> 16:06.008
He rapped his heart out.

16:06.182 --> 16:08.576
There was a verse about
Dracula doing the Jumble

16:08.750 --> 16:10.360
and the Wolfman
losing his briefcase.

16:10.534 --> 16:12.797
Finally,
his novelty-song mic drop.

16:12.972 --> 16:14.799
♪♪ The tracks wind left,
The tracks wind right

16:14.974 --> 16:16.410
♪♪ Chugga-chugga choo

16:16.584 --> 16:17.759
♪♪ This monster train
Will bite! ♪♪

16:17.933 --> 16:19.282
[RECORD SCRATCH]And thank you.

16:19.456 --> 16:20.936
Oh, I knew it!

16:21.110 --> 16:23.983
One verse in, and
the sultry vampiress loves it.

16:24.157 --> 16:25.723
I do not.

16:25.897 --> 16:27.290
What?
What's wrong with it, Elvira?

16:27.464 --> 16:30.380
First off, the monster train
is just a train.

16:30.554 --> 16:32.643
With monsters!
Hello?

16:32.817 --> 16:34.167
Why are they
on the train?

16:34.341 --> 16:36.473
To get to their
monster schools
and businesses downtown.

16:36.647 --> 16:38.214
So they live
in the suburbs?

16:38.388 --> 16:39.868
Obviously.

16:40.042 --> 16:41.696
Because the city has been
overrun by a bad element.

16:41.870 --> 16:43.654
Worse than monsters?

16:43.828 --> 16:45.569
Elvira, I can't believe
you're this literal.

16:45.743 --> 16:47.528
More like
Mistress of the Nitpick.

16:47.702 --> 16:49.834
Thank you both for being here
and happy Halloween.

16:52.446 --> 16:53.621
Okay,
you can't give up.

16:53.795 --> 16:55.275
Let's get back in the line

16:55.449 --> 16:56.276
and pretend
to be other people.What's the point?

16:56.450 --> 16:57.581
Geoff was right.

16:57.755 --> 16:59.235
This was just
a dumb idea.

16:59.409 --> 17:01.368
No, it's not.Joanne, it's over.

17:01.542 --> 17:03.413
I know it's silly.

17:03.587 --> 17:05.328
I used to think I'd be
so many things in life,

17:05.502 --> 17:07.896
a rapper, a pro athlete,
a business mogul.

17:08.070 --> 17:09.550
What kind of business?I don't know,

17:09.724 --> 17:11.117
and I'm clearly
never gonna find out.

17:11.291 --> 17:12.596
They're all just
stupid, childish dreams.

17:13.945 --> 17:15.251
Big Tasty's dead.

17:15.425 --> 17:16.818
Barry...Stop.

17:16.992 --> 17:18.820
You've done enough.

17:18.994 --> 17:20.561
I was supporting you.By making me
look like a fool?

17:20.735 --> 17:21.823
Thanks a lot.

17:21.997 --> 17:23.129
♪♪♪♪

17:26.871 --> 17:29.135
After his Halloween
humiliation at the mall,

17:29.309 --> 17:32.268
my brother Barry drowned his
troubles in an Orange Julius.

17:32.442 --> 17:34.749
Well, if it isn't
my little musical friend.

17:34.923 --> 17:36.316
Please,
I'm not in the mood.

17:36.490 --> 17:38.361
Wait, you eat food
like a real human?

17:38.535 --> 17:39.884
Are you even
a Mistress of the Dark?

17:40.059 --> 17:41.060
Well, occasionally,
I come into the light

17:41.234 --> 17:42.191
for a corn dog.

17:42.365 --> 17:44.280
Everything is wrong.

17:44.454 --> 17:45.847
I don't know
who I am anymore.

17:46.021 --> 17:47.675
It's just, I--

17:47.849 --> 17:51.722
I started to feel like
I was losing a part of myself,

17:51.896 --> 17:52.941
and the only person
who encouraged me

17:53.115 --> 17:54.377
to be that guy again
was my girlfriend.

17:54.551 --> 17:55.552
She sounds pretty great.

17:55.726 --> 17:56.684
She's the best,

17:56.858 --> 17:59.730
but I wasn't
very nice to her.

17:59.904 --> 18:01.297
Well, there's one thing
you can do.

18:01.471 --> 18:03.386
I'm not gonna date you
to make her jealous, Elvira.

18:03.560 --> 18:05.606
Any woman who would be
supportive of you

18:05.780 --> 18:07.738
after hearing that song
is worth holding on to.

18:11.525 --> 18:14.832
You are more than
the Mistress of the Dark.

18:15.006 --> 18:16.573
You are the mistress

18:16.747 --> 18:18.445
of insights
into the human heart.

18:18.619 --> 18:19.750
Thank you, Elvira.

18:19.924 --> 18:21.187
[SPOOKY ORGAN MUSIC PLAYS]

18:21.361 --> 18:23.667
Thank you,
odd boy in a mall.

18:28.281 --> 18:29.412
Hey.

18:29.586 --> 18:31.197
Hey.

18:31.371 --> 18:33.416
Bar, I'm sorry--Stop.

18:33.590 --> 18:35.157
You've got nothing
to be sorry for.

18:35.331 --> 18:37.333
I was afraid of
losing Big Tasty,

18:37.507 --> 18:38.987
and you were the only one
who cared enough

18:39.161 --> 18:40.858
to make sure I didn't.

18:41.032 --> 18:43.165
I would never let
Big Tasty die.

18:43.339 --> 18:44.514
He's a part of you.

18:44.688 --> 18:47.778
And I promise to support
all your crazy dreams, too.

18:47.952 --> 18:50.129
Good, because I got
a lot of them.

18:50.303 --> 18:52.479
Like, way too many.

18:52.653 --> 18:56.091
My rap name is
MC Joanne Rebecca Schwartz.

18:56.265 --> 18:58.049
You rap?I don't know,

18:58.224 --> 19:00.791
but I feel like I can
do anything with you.

19:02.228 --> 19:02.924
Me too.

19:04.969 --> 19:06.449
While Barry realized that
he had something

19:06.623 --> 19:08.321
more special than
a Halloween hit,

19:08.495 --> 19:10.627
I was still recovering
fromgetting hit.

19:10.801 --> 19:12.194
Oh, no.
What happened?

19:12.368 --> 19:13.369
I just
got clocked in the face

19:13.543 --> 19:14.849
with Pop-Pop's
albino pumpkin.

19:15.023 --> 19:16.285
Get over here.

19:16.459 --> 19:17.417
Yeah, well, uh,
here's the thing,

19:17.591 --> 19:19.070
it wasn't my pumpkin.

19:19.245 --> 19:21.116
I never had
a pumpkin.

19:21.290 --> 19:22.422
I made
the whole thing up.

19:22.596 --> 19:24.902
Ben, what did you do?

19:25.076 --> 19:26.382
I was just trying
to give the kid a Halloween

19:26.556 --> 19:28.341
like his other grandpa
used to.

19:28.515 --> 19:30.734
So the trash bags
and the going door-to-door?

19:30.908 --> 19:32.301
Eh, it was
the closest I could get

19:32.475 --> 19:33.737
to tricks, treats,
and whatnot.

19:33.911 --> 19:34.738
But like you said,
it was horrible.

19:34.912 --> 19:36.392
It wasn't great.

19:36.566 --> 19:38.525
But you tried.

19:38.699 --> 19:40.396
Yeah, and I screwed it up.
That's what I do.

19:40.570 --> 19:41.484
It's true,

19:41.658 --> 19:43.660
what Pops and I had
was special.

19:43.834 --> 19:45.271
But, trust me,

19:45.445 --> 19:46.750
this is a night
I'll never forget.

19:48.709 --> 19:51.407
Well, you might, after taking
that whack to your noggin,

19:51.581 --> 19:53.757
but, uh, I'll remember
for both of us.

19:56.630 --> 19:57.935
[CHUCKLES]

19:58.109 --> 20:00.286
Grandpa-grandson
Halloween love is real.

20:00.460 --> 20:02.026
Oh, this one,
blubbering over nothing.

20:02.201 --> 20:04.420
It's not nothing.Ahh.

20:04.594 --> 20:06.117
♪♪ They did the monster mash ♪♪

20:06.292 --> 20:07.684
Oh! Mama's coming in
for the candy pile.

20:07.858 --> 20:09.120
Oh!Yeah.

20:09.295 --> 20:11.079
♪♪ It was a graveyard smash ♪♪

20:11.253 --> 20:11.732
Turns out,
there's nothing like
a Halloween adventure

20:11.906 --> 20:12.776
to bring people together.

20:15.214 --> 20:16.693
And it doesn't matter
if you don't believe

20:16.867 --> 20:18.217
in ghosts and monsters,

20:18.391 --> 20:19.392
as long as you believe
in each other.Yes!

20:22.003 --> 20:24.092
Sure, no one can fill
the shoes of the people
we've lost...

20:25.441 --> 20:26.529
You're feeling better!

20:26.703 --> 20:27.835
And your costume
looks amazing!

20:28.009 --> 20:29.445
Your black eye
is so authentic.

20:29.619 --> 20:30.707
Pop-Pop helped me
with it.

20:30.881 --> 20:32.405
...but then again,

20:32.579 --> 20:34.711
sometimes new people help us
carry on old traditions.

20:34.885 --> 20:36.409
Nice.

20:36.583 --> 20:38.585
♪♪ First stop, second stop,
Third stop, fourth

20:38.759 --> 20:39.586
♪♪ Tracks run left ♪♪

20:39.760 --> 20:41.588
Especially the ones who
wouldn't dare give up.

20:45.244 --> 20:46.549
Trick or treat!

20:46.723 --> 20:47.768
Who are you
supposed to be?

20:47.942 --> 20:49.335
Girls holding pillowcases?

20:49.509 --> 20:51.032
No, you have to
have a costume.

20:51.206 --> 20:53.252
Fine. I'm her and she's me.

20:53.426 --> 20:55.732
You know, our dog walker's
termite specialist

20:55.906 --> 20:58.518
had a daughter who was
full of sassafras.

20:58.692 --> 21:00.955
One Halloween,
a wayward jellybean

21:01.129 --> 21:02.783
lodged in her ear canal.

21:02.957 --> 21:04.350
She lost her hearing,
her balance,

21:04.524 --> 21:06.221
then while scuba diving,

21:06.395 --> 21:08.049
she couldn't tell
which way was up

21:08.223 --> 21:11.357
and started going
deeper and deeper down.

21:11.531 --> 21:14.577
The pressure crushed her bones
like a soda can.

21:14.751 --> 21:18.102
Now she works at an arcade,
making change with her mouth.

21:18.277 --> 21:19.843
Any Smarties?Just take one.

21:20.931 --> 21:21.845
[BOTH SCREAM]

21:23.456 --> 21:24.457
Happy Halloween!

21:26.720 --> 21:27.895
Ooh.

